(thirdQuint)Palbociclib in Patients With Metastatic Castration-Resistant Prostate Cancer.

 The standard or usual treatment for this disease may be chemotherapy or other types of treatment to slow the spread of the disease and relieve some symptoms of cancer.

 Palbociclib is a new type of drug for prostate cancer.

 Laboratory tests show that it may help slow the growth of prostate cancer.

 Palbociclib has been shown to help patients with breast cancer but it is not known if the drug is useful for treating prostate cancer.

